This page covers the different ways in which you can create an **Animation Montage** using animation assets. 

## Steps

1. In the **Content Browser** of your project, click the **Add New** button (or right-click in the **Content Browser**) and choose **Animation** > **Animation Montage**.

	![](AddNewButton.png)

1. Select the **Skeleton** asset that you will want to use for the **Animation Montage**. 

	![](PickSkeleton.png)

1. Enter a name for your newly created **Animation Montage**. 

	![](NamedMontage.png)

1. Double-click to open your new Animation Montage to begin editing. 	
	
		
## End Result

After creating your Animation Montage, you can open it and it will appear empty (below). 

![](NewMontageOpened.png)

From here you can begin [editing your Animation Montage](Engine\Animation\AnimMontage\Editor) asset to reach your desired effect. 

You can also right-click any **Animation Sequence** asset and create an Animation Montage from the asset. 

![](RightClickExample.png)

When opening a Montage you have created from the right-click method, the animation will automatically be added to the Montage. 

![](RightClickExampleOpen.png)










